canonical_description: The processes and activities involved in researching, designing, building, training, and improving artificial intelligence technologies and applications, including their preparation for deployment.
rationale: Both refer to the same general process of creating AI technologies, differing only in wording and granularity.

canonical_description: The hardened, protective casing enclosing the pupa stage of a butterfly, within which metamorphosis occurs and from which the adult butterfly emerges.
rationale: Both entities share the same name, type, and describe the same protective pupa casing in the butterfly life cycle.
